<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911108-0063</DOCNO><DOCID>911108-0063.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- U.S. Shoe Corp.:   Firm Says Sales Eased 0.4%   In the Month Ended Nov. 2</HL><DATE>11/08/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B6A</SO><CO>   USR</CO><MS>CONSUMER CYCLICAL (CYC)</MS><IN>ALL SPECIALTY RETAILERS (RTS)SPECIALTY APPAREL RETAILERS (SAP)</IN><RE>NORTH AMERICA (NME)OHIO (OH)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   U.S. Shoe Corp., Cincinnati, Ohio, said sales in the monthended Nov. 2 were $166.4 million, down 0.4% from $167 milliona year earlier. Same-store sales fell 1.4%.   In the nine months ended Nov. 2, sales were $1.67 billion,up 4.3% from $1.6 billion a year earlier. Same-store salesfell 0.4%.</LP><TEXT>   In the month, women's-apparel sales were $99 million, down2.5% from the like period last year. Same-store sales fell0.4%. In the nine months, women's-apparel sales were $977million, up 4.1%. Same-store sales rose 2.8%.   For LensCrafters optical retailing, sales in the monthwere $44.8 million, up 7.7%. Same-store sales fell 0.3%. Inthe nine months, sales were $476 million, up 6.8%. Same-storesales fell 4%.   For footware, sales were $22.6 million in the month, down5.5%. Same-store sales fell 8.2%. In the nine months,footware sales were $216.8 million, down 0.5%. Same-storesales fell 6.5%.</TEXT></DOC>